HEADWORD: Copper-bottomed
<hw>Cop"per-bot`tomed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a
bottom made of copper, as a tin boiler or other vessel, or sheathed with
copper, as a ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

